{"title_page": "Kerrie Mengersen", "text_new": "{{short description|Australian statistician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Kerrie Mengersen\n| image       =  <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date |1962|1|1|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]\n| nationality = [[Australia]]n\n| fields      = [[Statistics]]\n| workplaces  = [[Queensland University of Technology]]<br/>[[University of Newcastle (Australia)|University of Newcastle]]<br/> [[Central Queensland University]]<br/>[[Bond University]]\n| alma_mater  = [[University of New England (Australia)|University of New England]]\n| thesis_title = Comparison and Selection of Populations with Special Reference to the Normal Distribution\n| thesis_url =  http://e-publications.une.edu.au/1959.11/16789\n| thesis_year = 1988\n| doctoral_advisors = [[Eve Bofinger]]<br/>[[Richard Tweedie]]\n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for   = \n| awards      = \n}}\n\n'''Kerrie Mengersen''' {{post-nominals|country=AUS|FAA}} (born 1962) is an [[Australia]]n [[Statistics|statistician]]. As of 2017, she is Distinguished Professor of Statistics at [[Queensland University of Technology]] in the Science and Engineering Faculty.<ref name=profile/><ref name=praise/>\n\nShe earned BA (Hons I) and PhD degrees in Mathematics, majoring in Statistics and Computing, from the [[University of New England (Australia)|University of New England]] (Armidale, New South Wales, Australia) in 1985 and 1989, respectively.<ref name=profile/>  She is the Director of the Bayesian Research and Applications Group (BRAG). This group is part of the Australian Research Council (ARC) Centre of Excellence for Mathematical and Statistical Frontiers (ACEMS) of Big Data, Big Models, New Insights.<ref name=bigdata/>\n\nShe has co-authored three books and edited two, and has written 27 book chapters and approximately 250 journal articles.<ref name=brag/><ref name=google/> Her research cuts across a broad spectrum of statistical practice. She is primarily known for her work in [[Bayesian statistics]] and [[meta-analysis]], and has worked in applications of statistics in [[medicine]] and [[environmental science]].<ref name=dp/> In 2016, she was the first woman to be awarded the Statistical Society of Australia's [[Pitman Medal]], which recognises outstanding achievement in the statistics discipline.<ref name=praise/> She talks about new challenges for statisticians in a YouTube video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EWeUvqGvgDc|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen Science Week 2015 Lecture at QUT|last=ACEMS - ARC Centre of Excellence for Mathematical & Statistical Frontiers|date=6 September 2015|via=YouTube|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124845/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EWeUvqGvgDc|archivedate=10 February 2018}}</ref> She has contributed to Australian [[biosecurity]] efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au/users/mengersenk.html|title=Mengersen \u2013 CRC for Plant Biosecurity|website=legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304222838/http://legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au/users/mengersenk.html|archivedate=2016-03-04}}</ref>\nIn October 2015 her research in building virtual [[habitat]]s was highlighted on the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-10-06/professor-kerrie-mengersen-qut-panoramic-camera-habitat-survey/6831284|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen with a panoramic camera that is helping to build virtual habitats.|date=6 October 2015|website=ABC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124845/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-10-06/professor-kerrie-mengersen-qut-panoramic-camera-habitat-survey/6831284|archivedate=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nMengersen was the National President of the Statistical Society of Australia (SSAI) in 2013, and was the International President of the [[International Society for Bayesian Analysis]] (ISBA) in 2016.<ref name=\"bayesian.org\"/>\n\n==Honors and awards==\n* 2014 Elected Fellow of the [[International Society for Bayesian Analysis]]<ref name=fellowsISBA/>\n* Elected Fellow of the [[Institute of Mathematical Statistics]]<ref name=fellows/>\n* Elected Fellow of the [[Society for Modelling and Simulation]]<ref name=sms/>\n* 2015 Biennial Medallist of the Modelling and Simulation Society of Australia and New Zealand (MSSANZ)<ref name=MSSANZ/>\n* 2015 [[Australian Research Council]] Laureate Fellowship<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arc.gov.au/news-media/media-releases/15-new-australian-laureate-fellows-announced|title=15 new Australian Laureate Fellows announced|last=Anonymous|date=23 June 2015|website=www.arc.gov.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318211940/http://www.arc.gov.au/news-media/media-releases/15-new-australian-laureate-fellows-announced|archivedate=18 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016 [[Statistical Society of Australia]] Pitman Medal<ref name=praise/>\n* 2018 Elected Fellow of the [[Australian Academy of Science]] (FAA)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.science.org.au/fellowship/fellows/professor-kerrie-mengersen|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen|website=www.science.org.au|access-date=2018-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616054726/https://www.science.org.au/fellowship/fellows/professor-kerrie-mengersen|archive-date=16 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=profile>{{cite web|url=http://staff.qut.edu.au/staff/mengerse/|title=QUT \u2013 Staff Profiles \u2013 Kerrie Mengersen|first=Mengersen|last=Kerrie|website=staff.qut.edu.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224193953/http://staff.qut.edu.au/staff/mengerse/|archivedate=2015-12-24}}</ref>\n<ref name=praise>{{cite web |url=https://www.qut.edu.au/news/news?news-id=112596 |title=High praise for QUT's new Distinguished Professor Kerrie Mengersen, now a Pitman Medallist |publisher=Queensland University of Technology |date=9 December 2016 |accessdate=22 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221013926/https://www.qut.edu.au/news/news?news-id=112596 |archivedate=21 December 2016 }}</ref>\n<ref name=dp>{{cite web|url=https://researchdata.ands.org.au/distinguished-professor-kerrie-mengersen/454004|title=Distinguished Professor Kerrie Mengersen|publisher=Research Data Australia|access-date=10 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124846/https://researchdata.ands.org.au/distinguished-professor-kerrie-mengersen/454004|archive-date=10 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=bigdata>{{cite web|url=http://www.statsoc.org.au/general/big-data-equals-good-news/|title=Big data equals good news|accessdate=5 January 2016|publisher=Statistical Society of Australia|date=19 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201103042/http://www.statsoc.org.au/general/big-data-equals-good-news/|archive-date=1 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=brag>{{cite web|url=https://bragqut.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/mengersen_cv-july2015.pdf|title=Curriculum vitae: Professor Kerrie Mengersen|accessdate=3 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304205403/https://bragqut.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/mengersen_cv-july2015.pdf|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=google>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=eiD83s4AAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao|title=Kerrie Mengersen \u2013 Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com.au|access-date=5 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203192518/https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=eiD83s4AAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao|archive-date=3 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=sms>{{cite web |url=http://www.springsim.org/Fellows |title=SCS Fellows Recognition |accessdate=15 January 2016|publisher=The Society for Modeling & Simulation International (SCS) |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082522/http://www.springsim.org/Fellows |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n<ref name=MSSANZ>{{cite web|url=http://www.mssanz.org.au/awards/medals.html|title=Awards \u2013 MSSANZ \u2013 Modelling and Simulation Society of Australia and New Zealand|website=www.mssanz.org.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160228011213/http://mssanz.org.au/awards/medals.html|archivedate=2016-02-28}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"bayesian.org\">{{cite web |url=http://bayesian.org/elections/2013/isba-president-elect/kerrie-mengersen|title=Kerrie Mengersen (president elect)|date=4 September 2013|publisher=International Society for Bayesian Analysis (ISBA)|accessdate=5 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222145904/http://bayesian.org/elections/2013/isba-president-elect/kerrie-mengersen|archive-date=22 February 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=fellows>{{cite web|url=http://imstat.org/awards/honored_fellows.htm|title=IMS Awards|website=imstat.org|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019175343/http://imstat.org/awards/honored_fellows.htm|archivedate=19 October 2016|access-date=19 June 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=fellowsISBA>{{cite web|url=https://bayesian.org/membership/isba-fellows/|title=ISBA fellows|publisher=International Society for Bayesian Analysis (ISBA)|accessdate=17 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180209063830/https://bayesian.org/membership/isba-fellows/|archive-date=9 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite book|last1=Mengersen|first1=Kerrie|title=Comparison and Selection of Populations with Special Reference to the Normal Distribution|series=Doctoral thesis|date=1988|publisher=University of New England|url=http://e-publications.une.edu.au/1959.11/16789}}\n*[https://acems.org.au/our-people/kerrie-mengersen Kerrie Mengersen Deputy director [[Australian Research Council Centre of Excellence for Mathematical and Statistical Frontiers|ACEMS]]]\n*[https://staff.qut.edu.au/staff/k.mengersen QUT: Distinguished Professor Kerrie Mengersen]\n*[https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=eiD83s4AAAAJ&hl=en Google Scholar: Kerrie Mengersen]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mengersen, Kerrie}}\n[[Category:Australian statisticians]]\n[[Category:Queensland University of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Women statisticians]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Institute of Mathematical Statistics| Institute of Mathematical Statistics]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:University of New England (Australia) alumni|University of New England (Australia)]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of grants/fellowships from the Australian Research Council (ARC)]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Statistical Society]]\n[[Category:Elected Members of the International Statistical Institute]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Australian Academy of Science]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Australian statistician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Kerrie Mengersen\n| image       =  <!--(filename only, i.e. without \"File:\" prefix)-->\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date |1962|1|1|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]]\n| nationality = [[Australia]]n\n| fields      = [[Statistics]]\n| workplaces  = [[Queensland University of Technology]]<br/>[[University of Newcastle (Australia)|University of Newcastle]]<br/> [[Central Queensland University]]<br/>[[Bond University]]\n| alma_mater  = [[University of New England (Australia)|University of New England]]\n| thesis_title = Comparison and Selection of Populations with Special Reference to the Normal Distribution\n| thesis_url =  http://e-publications.une.edu.au/1959.11/16789\n| thesis_year = 1988\n| doctoral_advisors = [[Eve Bofinger]]<br/>[[Richard Tweedie]]\n| doctoral_students = \n| known_for   = \n| awards      = \n}}\n\n'''Kerrie Mengersen''' {{post-nominals|country=AUS|FAA}} (born 1962) is an [[Australia]]n [[Statistics|statistician]]. As of 2017, she is Distinguished Professor of Statistics at [[Queensland University of Technology]] in the Science and Engineering Faculty.<ref name=profile/><ref name=praise/>\n\nShe earned BA (Hons I) and PhD degrees in Mathematics, majoring in Statistics and Computing, from the [[University of New England (Australia)|University of New England]] (Armidale, New South Wales, Australia) in 1985 and 1989, respectively.<ref name=profile/>  She is the Director of the Bayesian Research and Applications Group (BRAG). This group is part of the Australian Research Council (ARC) Centre of Excellence for Mathematical and Statistical Frontiers (ACEMS) of Big Data, Big Models, New Insights.<ref name=bigdata/>\n\nShe has co-authored three books and edited two, and has written 27 book chapters and approximately 250 journal articles.<ref name=brag/><ref name=google/> Her research cuts across a broad spectrum of statistical practice. She is primarily known for her work in [[Bayesian statistics]] and [[meta-analysis]], and has worked in applications of statistics in [[medicine]] and [[environmental science]].<ref name=dp/> In 2016, she was the first woman to be awarded the Statistical Society of Australia's [[Pitman Medal]], which recognises outstanding achievement in the statistics discipline.<ref name=praise/> She talks about new challenges for statisticians in a YouTube video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EWeUvqGvgDc|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen Science Week 2015 Lecture at QUT|last=ACEMS - ARC Centre of Excellence for Mathematical & Statistical Frontiers|date=6 September 2015|via=YouTube|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124845/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EWeUvqGvgDc|archivedate=10 February 2018}}</ref> She has contributed to Australian [[biosecurity]] efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au/users/mengersenk.html|title=Mengersen - CRC for Plant Biosecurity|website=legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304222838/http://legacy.crcplantbiosecurity.com.au/users/mengersenk.html|archivedate=2016-03-04}}</ref>\nIn October 2015 her research in building virtual [[habitat]]s was highlighted on the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-10-06/professor-kerrie-mengersen-qut-panoramic-camera-habitat-survey/6831284|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen with a panoramic camera that is helping to build virtual habitats.|date=6 October 2015|website=ABC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124845/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-10-06/professor-kerrie-mengersen-qut-panoramic-camera-habitat-survey/6831284|archivedate=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nMengersen was the National President of the Statistical Society of Australia (SSAI) in 2013, and was the International President of the [[International Society for Bayesian Analysis]] (ISBA) in 2016.<ref name=\"bayesian.org\"/>\n\n==Honors & Awards==\n* 2014 Elected Fellow of the [[International Society for Bayesian Analysis]]<ref name=fellowsISBA/>\n* Elected Fellow of the [[Institute of Mathematical Statistics]]<ref name=fellows/>\n* Elected Fellow of the [[Society for Modelling and Simulation]]<ref name=sms/>\n* 2015 Biennial Medallist of the Modelling and Simulation Society of Australia and New Zealand (MSSANZ)<ref name=MSSANZ/>\n* 2015 [[Australian Research Council]] Laureate Fellowship<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arc.gov.au/news-media/media-releases/15-new-australian-laureate-fellows-announced|title=15 new Australian Laureate Fellows announced|last=Anonymous|date=23 June 2015|website=www.arc.gov.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318211940/http://www.arc.gov.au/news-media/media-releases/15-new-australian-laureate-fellows-announced|archivedate=18 March 2016}}</ref>\n* 2016 [[Statistical Society of Australia]] Pitman Medal<ref name=praise/>\n* 2018 Elected Fellow of the [[Australian Academy of Science]] (FAA)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.science.org.au/fellowship/fellows/professor-kerrie-mengersen|title=Professor Kerrie Mengersen|website=www.science.org.au|access-date=2018-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616054726/https://www.science.org.au/fellowship/fellows/professor-kerrie-mengersen|archive-date=16 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=profile>{{cite web|url=http://staff.qut.edu.au/staff/mengerse/|title=QUT - Staff Profiles - Kerrie Mengersen|first=Mengersen|last=Kerrie|website=staff.qut.edu.au|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224193953/http://staff.qut.edu.au/staff/mengerse/|archivedate=2015-12-24}}</ref>\n<ref name=praise>{{cite web |url=https://www.qut.edu.au/news/news?news-id=112596 |title=High praise for QUT's new Distinguished Professor Kerrie Mengersen, now a Pitman Medallist |publisher=Queensland University of Technology |date=9 December 2016 |accessdate=22 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221013926/https://www.qut.edu.au/news/news?news-id=112596 |archivedate=21 December 2016 }}</ref>\n<ref name=dp>{{cite web|url=https://researchdata.ands.org.au/distinguished-professor-kerrie-mengersen/454004|title=Distinguished Professor Kerrie Mengersen|publisher=Research Data Australia|access-date=10 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210124846/https://researchdata.ands.org.au/distinguished-professor-kerrie-mengersen/454004|archive-date=10 February 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n<ref name=bigdata>{{cite web|url=http://www.statsoc.org.au/general/big-data-equals-good-news/|title=Big data equals good news|accessda